The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, September 28, 2004 

 Drug drink duo caught

 Calcutta, Sept. 27: Sealdah division?s Railway Protection Force has claimed to have busted a racket in robbing passengers by selling or offering them drugged cold drinks and packaged fruit drinks.

 S.Z. Samuel, the chief security commissioner of the RPF, today said that Raju Naskar and Mohamed Mustak, who boarded the Sealdah-Asansol fast train around 2 pm yesterday, were caught red-handed while trying to rob one Bhelu Ram of Rs 5,000, two handbags and watches after drugging him. 




